properties.Title: Bill Rubin's Warren Night School, Vol 3.
properties.Description:
Join us for Elizabeth Warren Night School Vol. 3, taught by DC attorney Bill Rubin. Warren Night School will be a reoccurring monthly event happening at our campaign office in Concord to learn more about the big, structural change that Elizabeth is fighting for in New Hampshire, and how you can be a part of our grassroots movement.

Last Warren Night School was a huge success! We'll be able to give you the resources you need to have more productive conversations with your relatives, friends and neighbors as you spread the word about Elizabeth and her plans.

Bill Rubin was an organizer for Barack Obama’s presidential campaign in 2008. He joined the Obama Administration in 2009 as General Counsel of the Peace Corps. He later worked in the Civil Rights Division of the Department of Justice on education discrimination issues and in the Office of the Pardon Attorney on President Obama’s clemency initiative for non-violent drug offenders. For the 2016 presidential election, he directed the get-out-the-vote operation for Hillary Clinton’s campaign in western PA.

If you have any accessibility needs, please let us know so that we can make sure the event will be accessible and comfortable for you. You can contact either our Concord-based organizer Sarah Nesbit (email snesbit@elizabethwarren.com or phone/text 803 543 8487) or our community organizer Bill Rubin (email bill@mwrubin.com or phone/text 857 928 7053).
